reviews.text: We ordered at 12:57pm. Nothing showed up, not even the soup nor drinks. We asked for a follow up at 1:20pm. We asked for a second follow up at 1:28pm. A waiter said that their computer was broken down in the morning and nothing was sent to the kitchen. 1:43pm we had the first pizza. The tables around us were suffering from the same problem. The manager never showed up to explain why. So much for a $320 (for 2) lunch.

We were a large group and ordered several dishes. Except for the pasta with tequila which was a stand-out, the rest of the food was barely restaurant quality. The ribs were dry and under-spiced. The pizzas were tasteless with barely prepared sauce and chewy toppings. The pastas were overdone and dry. The salad greens were not fresh with the chicken dry and over-done. The service is good and friendly. All they need to do is find people who can cook.

This was terrible service all around. We showed up at 6:45 it was 7:30 before food arrived. The steak was burnt, then the other food trickled in around 7:45 with the last pasta dish being served at 8 pm. The pizza was barely cooked and in general this was the worst. Dont go here. Seriously

This place has long queue but average food . We have to wait for table around 1 hour and got served by very unprofessional way . We ordered set for 4 dinner . After 10 minutes meat balls ana pizza came out . Remaining 1 apetizer , 2 pasta , ribeye and 1 salad never showed up before we have to make enquiry after 30 minutes . Don't even bother going here .....
Like it as usual. Love my favorite spinach dip.
